PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This longitudinal study of a national sample examined the effects of workers? gender and race on their entrance into managerial positions in public and private organizations over a period of four years. Results suggested that black workers had promotion advantages in both sectors and that women had promotion advantages in the private sector.
AB  - This longitudinal study of a national sample examined the effects of workers? gender and race on their entrance into managerial positions in public and private organizations over a period of four years. Results suggested that black workers had promotion advantages in both sectors and that women had promotion advantages in the private sector.
